metadata.name: Kinetograms #405
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: The Space Inside #264
metadata.description:
Points fill in shapes on a warped noise field. The resulting images range from soft water colors to distorted, pixelated CRT screens. 

The image is drawn at 3000x3000px and scaled to the browser size. 

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 3000x3000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Features:
- Two palette sets
- Light or dark background
- 70% color image, 30% monochrome
- Various combinations of circles and rectangles
- All rectangles 
- 7 types of shapes: random circles, packed circles, checkerboard, orbs, ring, spiral, checkerboard and orbs
- Rectangles snap to a grid
- Fuzzy lines connected groups of drawing points
- Fuzzy lines around the dots
- Bright border on the shapes

Rare
- 9% to have a soft monochrome and color palette

metadata.name: Love #154
metadata.description:
We all experience love at different scales, ranging from scarcely perceived instances of kindness to unforgettable affections shown to us by family and friends, pets and partners. Each of these moments link us to the same boundless and enveloping interconnectedness that persists across space and time: the infinite source of our deepest aspirations.

Like the feeling of simple bliss, ‘Love’ portrays the visceral radiant light and warmth of our innermost joys. By taking a moment to open ourselves up, these swirling worlds of weightless and seemingly infinite brush strokes invite us to slow down and dwell in prismatic intuitive swells.

In doing so, we may find the immense and omnipresent love that needs only our awareness to be felt.

__________

Press 1-9 to load at different scales (1 = 2,000x2,000 (default), 9 = 10,000x10,000)
When zoomed in, once the output is fully loaded, you can click and drag to move around the canvas
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'B' to toggle the background texture on or off
Press 'A' to toggle the loading animation (recommended for very large scales)

Created with p5.js
For third party license information, please see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt
__________
TENDER x teaboswell
May 2022

metadata.name: Hatch Field 001 #240
metadata.description:
Genesis p5js drawing on fx(hash). Experimenting with translating recent work in done in Grasshopper exploring hatch patterns to p5.js. By Andrew Kudless / Matsys @matsysdesign
There are four feature groups:
- Base Hue: Red, Orange, Yellow, Spring Green, Green, Ocean Green, Cyan, Sky Blue, Blue, Purple, Magenta, and Crimson. Each has the same random chance of being the base color (12%).
- Hue Range: Narrow (14%), Wide (51%), and Infinite(34%)
- Lineweight: Thin (75%), Medium (10%), Thick (10%), Extra Thick (5%)
-Fray: Loose (90%), Tight (10%)

metadata.name: Traces #66
metadata.description:
Traces is an exploration around movement.
Inspired but motion blur in photography, using lines travelling through obstacles, it can create scenes, sometimes representation of virtual landscapes.

Its features include:
- A choice between 12 modern and 7 rarer palette inspired by some of my photographies (revealed on my twitter with the first mint
- 3 definitions
- 3 types of obstacles modifying the motion
- Rare symmetrical dispositions

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

Unsold will be burnt after a certain time, and price might increase

metadata.name: Breeding Grounds #308
metadata.description:
Social Networks.
Molecular Clouds.
Neuronal Circuitries.
Quantum Mechanical Structures.

Blurring Boundaries.
Infinite Self-Similarities.

Total.
Mess.

Perfect.
Order.

/////
Each element (besides the painting ground textures) is based on the underlying subdivided grid which is sometimes exposed like some kind of preliminary drawing.

Note on the split:
After seeing some of the outputs, Sermin had a dream about “Breeding Grounds” and I decided to incorporate events and feelings from her dream into the project. That's how the names of the color palettes came about. Thank you for naming them, Sermin!

Press 's' to save a .png with the current resolution (2000x3000).
If you want a file with higher resolution and/or without the “Painting Ground Textures” for printing please contact me via Twitter or Discord.

metadata.name: Nil #107
metadata.description:
A balanced combination of spatial subdivision and algorithm sonification. A subdivision surface algorithm is recursive in nature: the process starts with a base level of area, and a refinement scheme is then applied to this field. This process takes that element and subdivides it, creating new segmented areas. The positions of the new areas are computed based on the positions of nearby old fields, edges, and/or faces. A cellular automata is running on the texture of some of these areas, building continuous, tautological worlds of binary patterns and relationships. Thus, unfolding of a pixel’s ‘umwelt’ can be witnessed through the slow, contemplative process.

The audio synthesis consists of a stochastic melody that emerges along the division of the new areas and territories within the image structure. This melody is complemented with tiny micro sounds, triggered by each new generation of the surface mounted cellular automata. 

Touch to listen
